The paper deals with low-rank recovery and clustering applications of PCA, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG, cs.CV). The use of graphs in the recovery method suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The introduction of a RIP condition for low-rank matrices and the use of efficient sampling techniques suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
